      description:
          "7 Days Big five Uganda Chimpanzee and Gorilla Tracking Safari\n\nUganda is entitled to the best experience while on a 7 Days Big five Uganda Chimpanzee and Gorilla Tracking Safari where you get the best of the best with all the big five wildlife game drives added with gorilla and Chimpanzee Tracking.\n\nTour and Travel Company: Wild Travel Safaris & Adventures\n\nWebsite: https://wildtravelsafaris.com/\n\nEmail: info@wildtravelsafaris.com\n\n\n\nDay 1: Transfer to Murchison Falls Park en route to Rhino Sanctuary\n\nYour safari in Uganda will begin with driving northwards to Murchison falls National Park. With a hot lunch en route prepare yourselves for the breathtaking scenery and a short nature walk to the Ziwa Rhino sanctuary in Masindi.\n\nThe guided nature walk in the sanctuary brings you up close to the endangered rhinos. In the evening arrive at the national park and transfer directly to your lodge for dinner and overnight at your accommodation preference\n\nAccommodation: Pakuba Lodge Fort Murchison lodges.\n\n\n\nDay 2: Activities in Murchison Falls Park\n\nAfter early morning breakfast enjoy an early game drive and enjoy some of the vast array of game animals like giraffes elephants and buffalo that roam the park. Return to Lodge for Lunch.\nIn the afternoon take a Boat Launch upstream to the foot of the thundering Murchison Falls offering great photo opportunities of this marvel of nature. Also along the banks of the River you will be able to see animals like Hippos crocodiles and unique bird species for the avid Bird watchers.\n\n\n\nDay 3: Transfer from Murchison Falls to Kibale Forests\n\nAfter an early breakfast leave the national park and proceed in the direction of Fort Portal traversing along the Great Rift Valley and the Rwenzori Mountain ranges could be seen at a good range as you progress to Fort Portal town. Lunch en–route.\n\nHave an Evening Bigodi Nature walk then later Check-in for overnight and dinner at your accommodation preference\n\nAccommodation: Isunga Lodge Kibale Forest Camp Papaya Lake Lodge.\n\n\n\nDay 4: Chimpanzee tracking and later Transfer to Queen Elizabeth Park\n\nAfter an early breakfast continue to the Chimpanzee Tracking Headquarters for a briefing open to meet up with the world’s 99% Human Apes. “Chimpanzees are also one of the largest primates in the world.\n\nAfter your back have lunch and continue further down following the mystical mountain ranges to Queen Elizabeth National Park for an afternoon safari by boat on the Kazinga channel connecting both Lake George and Edward. This evening spend the time off at leisure and later prepare for dinner and overnight at an accommodation of your choice.\n\nAccommodation: Bush Lodge Elephant Hub Ihamba Safari Lodge.\n\nDay 5: Queen Elizabeth Safari activities and transfer to Bwindi via the Ishasha Sector\n\n\n\nThis morning after your early breakfast have another game drive in the North of the park and have a chance to spot the Uganda Kobs elephants and lions and later after lunch depart the northern side of the park and drive southwards to the Ishasha sector the area famed for the tree-climbing lions.\n\nAs you drive through you may see wildlife and also tree-climbing lions. Spend the rest of the evening with another game drive and try out your luck. Then drive to Bwindi Forests to your lodge at leisure for dinner and overnight.\n\nAccommodation: Bakiga Lodge.\n\nDay 6: Gorilla Tracking Day\n\nThis after your breakfast heads to the Uwa headquarters for the gorilla tracking briefing. So as to see the rarest endangered animals and the most specifical highlights of the country Uganda.\n\nThe Mountains gorillas and the tracking will take about 6-7 hours long from the start times. Return to your lodging for an overnight\n\nDay 7: Transfer back to Entebbe\n\nThis morning have breakfast at leisure and later transfer back to Kampala with lunch en-route and wonderful photography at the equator. This day is reserved for evening flights through Entebbe International airport.\n\n\n\nEnd of the 7 Days Big five Uganda Chimpanzee and Gorilla Tracking Safari\n\nIncluded on a 7 Days Big five Uganda Chimpanzee and Gorilla Tracking Safari;Park fees\n\n\n\nAll activities\n\nGorilla Permits at \$700 per person\n\nChimpanzee Permits at \$200 per person\n\nAll accommodation(Unless listed as upgrade)\n\nA professional driver/guide\n\nAll transportation(Unless labeled as optional)\n\nAll Taxes/VAT\n\nRound trip airport transfer\n\nMeals(As specified in the day-by-day section)\n\nWater in the Vehicle Drinks\n\nExcludes the safaris \n\n\n\nInternational flights(From/to home) Additional accommodation before and at the end of the tour Tips(Tipping guidelines) Personal items Souvenirs travel insurance visa fees Government imposed increase of taxes and/or park fees.\n\n\n"),
